{"body": "Object#method(name) is defined.\r\n\r\nWhen trying to backport this to rails 3.2 it gave me a little grief.\r\n\r\nCan we pick a different name for it?\r\n\r\nThe documentation seems to call it index_type for both postgres and my sql. While I don't like having the word index twice (IndexDefinition#index_type), it is more rails friendly than overriding Object#method.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, the create index code currently uses an index_type variable to specify unique. IndexDefinition uses 'unique' for this purpose, so it is only a local variable in 2 places. But a side note none the less\r\n\r\n\r\nThoughts?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9059064", "created_at": "2012-10-02T05:04:02Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6101#issuecomment-9059064", "updated_at": "2012-10-02T05:08:37Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6101, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kbrock/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kbrock/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kbrock/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kbrock", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kbrock/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/kbrock", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kbrock/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/cf358de2534f820f5342180bb0e861ef?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F29530de21430b7540ec3f65135f7323c.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kbrock/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kbrock/received_events", "gravatar_id": "cf358de2534f820f5342180bb0e861ef", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kbrock/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "kbrock", "type": "User", "id": 1930, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kbrock/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52380dc2bd3543c15100d33f"}, "id": 9059064, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rail